The Taiwan CDC established a 3-tier framework for the
national stockpile in 2003 and implemented a replacement
model for PPE in 2011. This replacement model has been
proven to be more economical and efﬁcient over traditional
purchasing practices as a way to renew the central stockpile,
and it could also serve as emergency support in an epidemic
situation and the basis of international cooperation. In the
future, we will continuously improve our system by re-
viewing the operational outcomes of these contracts and
evaluating the potential needs for different categories of
PPE in response to various infectious diseases.
